events.name: Boston Celtics at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 34 points, including the tiebreaking jumper with 33 seconds left, Jaylen Brown added 29 and the Boston Celtics beat the San Antonio Spurs 121-116 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum, Brown help Celtics escape with 121-116 win over Spurs

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine made three consecutive 3-pointers during a key fourth-quarter stretch and scored 36 points, DeMar DeRozan had 35 and the Chicago Bulls beat the Utah Jazz 126-118 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine, DeRozan team to help Bulls beat Jazz, 126-118

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 34 points, 10 rebounds and 10 assists for his ninth triple-double of the season, Christian Wood added 28 points and the Dallas Mavericks outlasted the short-handed New Orleans Pelicans 127-117 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic scores 34 points in triple-double, Mavs beat Pelicans

events.name: Orlando Magic at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Just when the defending champion Warriors welcomed back some reinforcements, Klay Thompson's surgically repaired left knee required a break.
headlines.shortLinkText: Banchero, Franz Wagner lead Magic past undermanned Warriors

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — LeBron James scored 37 points, Dennis Schroder made two free throws with 3.6 seconds left and the Los Angeles Lakers beat the Sacramento Kings 136-134 on Saturday night for their fifth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron James scores 37 points, Lakers beat Kings 136-134
